						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1469, Plavaṅga, Phālguṇa, śu. • • • (= A.D. 1548 February),</hi> in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Sadāśiva-Ma[hārāya].</hi> It records that <hi rend="bold">Timmōja, Koṇḍōja</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Bhadrōja</hi> got a grant from the king exempting the barbers of <hi rend="bold">Maidūru</hi> from the payment of <hi rend="italic">kāṇike, kaḍḍāya</hi> and other taxes.</p>						

